  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Ideal Sedation for Stroke Thrombectomy (ISST) registry will answer the key questions
      whether sedation with intubation and paralytics is feasible and whether it delays the time to
      recanalization in comparison with conscious sedation alone. As a pilot registry, it is
      anticipated to enroll 40 acute stroke patients requiring mechanical thrombectomy over 12-18
      months. Following enrollment, data will be collected prospectively from medical records and
      from patients' visits.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
